# 1. 嬉しい知らせ

Saki: You're on this page, Hona! You look so focused and cool.
Ichika: It's from one of our performances. Oh, there's even an introductory blurb...
Ichika: “The leader of one of the bands that everyone's been talking about lately, Leo/need. Her bandmates trust her deeply...”
Honami: Th-That's a little embarrassing...
Ichika: Really? I think it's perfect.
Shiho: You and Saki are way too excited about this, Ichika. I mean, this isn't the first time we've appeared in a magazine.
Saki: Yeah, but... This one feels special!
Saki: Because it's Leo/need's first time on the cover!
Ichika: We've had small sections and short interviews before, but being on the cover does make this feel special.
Honami: Speaking of which... Ichika, didn't you buy two copies?
Ichika: Yeah, I did. One to read at home, and one to preserve.
Shiho: Preserve? You don't normally do that.
Ichika: It's because this one also has a special VIRTUAL SINGER section.
Ichika: I was just so happy that I got to appear in the same magazine as Miku...
Shiho: Alright, that makes sense.
Honami: Hehe. I agree.
Honami: Speaking of Miku... They had some information on the Fan Festival, right?
Saki: Oh, Ichi, you performed in that way back when!
Ichika: Yeah. I won't be in it this year, but I still plan on going.
Shiho: You sure keep busy when it comes to these things, Ichika. Don't you also have a Miku concert lined up soon?
Ichika: That's right. It's not as big as the Fan Festival, but I'm really excited about it.
Ichika: Oh, there's the bell... We should probably start heading back.
Shiho: Alright, see you all later. We're heading over to the office after school, right?
Honami: Yes. Mr. Shindo said that he has something very important to tell us.
Saki: What if it's about our next festival? Or another cover shoot!
Shiho: We're not going to get another cover offer just like that.
Saki: Hey, you never know! After all, we're “one of the bands that everyone's been talking about”♪
Shiho: Alright, I get it.
Honami: I don't know what he's going to tell us, but I hope it's good news.
Honami: Wait, Mr. Shindo, did you just say...?
Shindo: I understand why you're all surprised.
Shindo: So, allow me to repeat what I just said.
Shindo: Your solo show is set to go.
Ichika: A...
Saki: A solo show...!
Shindo: That's right. It's actually been in the works for quite a while now...
Shindo: But the venue we've been in talks with finally has an opening. Now we can say for sure that you'll be playing there.
Shiho: By the way, which venue?
Shindo: TONE BASE Shibuya.
Honami: Wait, haven't a lot of famous bands played there on tours?
Shindo: Yes. It isn't just famous amongst music lovers. It has high name recognition even with the wider public.
Shindo: If you include standing room only, it holds about 1,500 people. I'd say it's the perfect venue for your band right now.
Ichika: 1,500...
Shindo: You have about two months to prepare for it.
Shindo: I know it's a bit of a tight schedule. However, putting on a successful show at TONE BASE will be a fantastic feather in your cap.
Shindo: We promise to give you all the support we can, so let's make sure it goes well.
Everyone: Of course!
Honami: (This is incredible... On top of being on the cover of a magazine, we get to do a solo show...)
Honami: (Things are going to get very busy, but we need to do our best. This is our chance to have our music heard by even more people.)
